                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/387.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Extracts.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Porras party committee has left a petition, which goes in the pouch tomorrow,
                    requesting supervision by the United States of the registration of voters, in
                    view of the grave electoral situation and in order to give proper guaranties to
                    their opponents; such supervision to begin as soon as possible, as registration
                    will close on May 15. The petition also requests supervision by the United
                    States of both the municipal elections (June 30) and the presidential elections
                    (July 14 and August 2). Numerous supporting documents accompany the
                    petition,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
